            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-147-person1412">
                  DAVID 
                  EVANS
               <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1412" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1412" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Chatham-gardens, City-road. On the 3d of February, about eleven o'clock at night, I was called up by a young man; I went out, and found the prisoner in the privy - he lived in the gardens, about sixty yards off; he had no business there. I asked him how he came so near home to do this; he said</p>
               <p>"Mr. Evans you won't hurt me, will you." I found the box, some memorandums, and a bottle in his pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-147-person1413">
                  THOMAS 
                  DUNNING
               <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1413" type="surname" value="DUNNING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1413" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1413" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. Evans called me; I found the prisoner in the privy, and the rest of the property tied up in an apron, which he claimed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-147-person1414">
                  JOHN 
                  PITT
               <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1414" type="surname" value="PITT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1414" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-147-person1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Chatham-gardens; the prisoner had no right on my premises; this property was in a summer house, which I locked at eight o'clock that night. I found four squares of glass broken in the window, by which means he could get this.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I found them in the road.</p>
